Police say an argument broke out between the man and his colleagues at Zebediela Citrus and he allegedly shot four people. JOHANNESBURG - Limpopo police are searching for a man who opened fire on colleagues during a meeting on Thursday morning.The police's Moatshe Ngoepe says an argument broke out between the man and his colleagues at Zebediela Citrus and he allegedly shot four people before running away.He says the victims, who sustained serious injuries, are being treated at a nearby hospital while investigations continue. We are therefore calling on the man from Polokwane to avail himself to the Zebediela police station or the nearest station to assist us in the investigations. 